de.frauas.jdemandmodel.appliance

Enum Device

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Device>
      • de.frauas.jdemandmodel.appliance.Device
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Device>

    public enum Device
extends java.lang.Enum<Device>
    This enum type lists the names, activity value and row of all appliances. The activity value is used to retrieve statistical data of when this appliance is used from a file (see ActivityReader. The row indicates where to find the appliance's other data in another file (see ApplianceReader). There is a static method to translate device strings into an array of devices.
    Author:
    lukas

      • getDevices

        public static Device[] getDevices(java.lang.String[] stringArray)

        This method is designed especially for being used by the Parser and the Main, that will call the ApplianceManager constructor with the result. If any of the strings equals "none", a null pointer will be returned and an empty string array will result in an empty device array.

        Any invalid strings will result in a warning and add a trailing null pointer to the returned device array (this is handled in the ApplianceManager constructor, but must be taken care of when using the method in any other context!). Finally, if only invalid strings were passed (excluding "none"), an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        stringArray - strings representing Devices, that appear in the result
        Returns:
        an array of the devices represented by the parameter strings.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if only invalid strings were passed.
